---
import StaticArticlePage from '@/components/ui/StaticArticlePage.astro'
import { getTermsHref } from '@/lib/terms-links'
---

<StaticArticlePage
  description="Plain-language terms for using SeniorPath."
  englishHref={getTermsHref('en')}
  kicker="Legal"
  portugueseHref={getTermsHref('pt-br')}
  title="Terms and Conditions"
>
  <h2>What SeniorPath is</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath is an editorial learning site. It publishes guides, concepts, glossary entries, and curated paths
    meant to help people think more clearly about software work. The site does not currently require an account to
    browse its public content.
  </p>

  <h2>How you may use it</h2>
  <p>
    You may read, share links to, and use the material for personal learning, team discussion, and professional
    development. You may not try to disrupt the site, scrape it in an abusive way, republish large portions as
    your own work, or misuse any commenting features if they are enabled.
  </p>

  <h2>Content and responsibility</h2>
  <p>
    The content is educational and reflects editorial judgment. It can change as ideas are clarified, corrected,
    expanded, or reorganized. Nothing on the site should be treated as legal, financial, security, hiring, or
    business advice for a specific situation. You are responsible for how you apply anything you read here.
  </p>

  <h2>External services and comments</h2>
  <p>
    Some pages may link to outside resources or load third-party services, such as article comments. Those
    services have their own terms and policies, and SeniorPath cannot control how they operate.
  </p>

  <h2>Availability and changes</h2>
  <p>
    SeniorPath may add, remove, rename, or restructure pages, features, and sections at any time. The site is
    provided as it exists today, without a guarantee that every page, route, or feature will always stay the same
    or remain available.
  </p>

  <h2>Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the extent allowed by law, SeniorPath is not responsible for indirect loss, business interruption, or
    decisions made from interpreting or applying the content. The practical rule is simple: use the material as a
    learning resource, not as a substitute for your own judgment.
  </p>
</StaticArticlePage>
